{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the 'rawcontinue' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for 'continue' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"5987136":{"pageid":5987136,"ns":0,"title":"Tommy (comics)","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"{{mergeto|List of Marvel Comics characters: T|date=December 2012}}\n\n{{Superherobox| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics-->\nimage=[[Image:tommymorlock1.jpg|200px]]\n|caption= Tommy\n|comic_color=background:#ff8080\n|character_name=Tommy\n|real_name=unrevealed\n|species=[[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|Human Mutant]]\n|publisher=[[Marvel Comics]]\n|debut=''Uncanny X-Men'' #210 (Oct 1986)\n|creators=[[Chris Claremont]] and [[John Romita, Jr.]]\n|alliance_color=background:#cccccc\n|alliances=[[Morlocks (comics)|Morlocks]]\n|aliases=\n|powers=ability to become two-dimensional.\n|}}\n\n'''Tommy''' is a [[Marvel Comics]] mutant, who first appeared in ''[[Uncanny X-Men]]'' #210.\n\n==Publication history==\nTommy appeared in ''[[Uncanny X-Men]]'' #210 (October 1986), and was created by [[Chris Claremont]] and [[John Romita, Jr.]]\n\nTommy appeared as part of the \"Morlocks\" entry in the ''[[Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Deluxe Edition]]'' #18.\n\n==Fictional character biography==\n[[Image:Tommymorlock2.jpg|left|thumb| Tommy ]]Tommy is a young [[Morlocks (comics)|Morlock]] living under the streets of New York. She flees the city after the [[Marauders (comics)|Marauders]] kill some of her Morlock friends under as yet undetailed circumstances. She is rescued by the [[Hellfire Club (comics)|Hellfire Club]] mercenary Richard Salmons and brought to Los Angeles, where the Marauders track her down. Stunned by one of [[Harpoon (comics)|Harpoon's]] spears, Richard begs Tommy to give him his gun. Tommy panicks and flees, abandoning Richard, who was soon afterwards shot by [[Scalphunter (comics)|Scalphunter]].<ref>''Uncanny X-Men'' #210</ref>\n\nTommy hitchhikes a train ride back to New York. She is trailed by some of the Marauders to 'The Alley', the Morlock home in the New York sewer tunnels. Just when Tommy is about to flee into the tunnels, she is incapacitated by Harpoon and then shot by Scalphunter<ref>''Uncanny X-Men'' #210</ref> off-panel.  She was the first person to die in the [[Mutant Massacre|Marvel Mutant Massacre]].\n\n==Powers and abilities==\n*Tommy had the ability to become two-dimensional.\n\n==Retcon==\n* Although ''Uncanny X-Men'' #210 shows that the Marauders followed her into the Alley, Marvel has [[retcon]]ned the events of the Mutant Massacre to say that [[Gambit (comics)|Gambit]] was responsible for leading the Marauders to the Alley.<ref>''Uncanny X-Men'' #350</ref>\n\n==Other media==\n===Television===\n* Tommy appears in the ''[[X-Men (TV series)|X-Men]]'' episode \"Captive Hearts.\" She is among the featured Morlocks that fight the X-Men. In \"Secrets Not Long Buried,\" Tommy is one of the many residents of the mutant-dominated community of Skull Mesa.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{marveldatabase|Tommy}}\n* [[MarvelDatabase:Character Gallery Tommy]]\n* {{Marvunapp|http://www.marvunapp.com/Appendix3/tommymorlock.htm|Tommy}}\n\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics superheroes]]\n\n{{Marvel-hero-stub}}"}]}}}}